  ?part rdfs:label ?partLabel .
  # then in your reasoning: normalised = ?v * factor(?u)   # factor from the unit
} ORDER BY DESC(?v)
```
The DIRECT (one hop) constituents of a whole and their stated best amounts, with units. Starts from an INSTANCE whose label is known (instances carry labels; classes do not). The whole reaches its statement via futuram:hasCompositionStatement; each part is a futuram:PartRelation (hasPartRelation) whose futuram:refersTo names the constituent and whose futuram:hasQuantity carries the amount. NOTE the unit column: amounts come in more than one qudt:unit — do not compare them without normalising each by its unit's factor. The FILTER literal is a placeholder; substitute the user's term.:

```sparql
